      • run

        public final void run()
        Main entry point into the actor: the ActorCell is a Runnable that is enqueued in its Executor whenever it needs to run. The _status field is used for coordination such that it is never enqueued more than once at any given time, because that would break the Actor Model.

        The idea here is to process at most as many messages as were in queued upon entry of this method, interleaving each normal message with the processing of all system messages that may have accumulated in the meantime. If at the end of the processing messages remain in the queue then this cell is rescheduled.

        All coordination occurs via a single Int field that is only updated in wait-free manner (LOCK XADD via unsafe.getAndAddInt), where conflicts are resolved by compensating actions. For a description of the bit usage see the companion object&rsquo;s source code.

        Specified by:
        run in interface java.lang.Runnable
